*notices claptoan* Wet me begin by saying this piece is in nyo way designyed to sewve as an attack on the membews of this communyity, wathew, I wouwd wike to say these things in an effowt to inspiwe peopwe to think cwiticawwy about the function this and othew onwinye spaces. When I was 11 I twied, and faiwed, to pick up acoustic guitaw. Aftew giving up, I wesowved awound age 14 to join my high schoow's jazz band and began taking bass wessons whiwe teaching mysewf guitaw. Since then, pwacticing has been a daiwy woutinye and wwiting music has become a deep passion of minye. Eawwy on, I stwuggwed, as does evewyonye. But soon fwustwation gave way to dedication, and I began to nyote exponyentiaw impwuvment in my abiwities uvw time. My fiwst obsession suwwounded the minyow pentatonyic scawe. I compuwsivewy wistenyed to and studied the music of Cweam, and to this day Ewic Cwapton's wowk fwom the mid/wate 1960's has fowmed the cownyewstonye of my stywe of pwaying in this scawe. My band's instwuctow spent yeaws fwustwated by my pewsonyaw appwoach to music, twying to get me to stick to bass and focus my guitaw pwaying on whythm and jazz chowds; I fought evewy day to wetain what I saw as my unyique identity as a musician, that of a kind of psych-wevivawist. Eventuawwy I began to bwanch out into othew scawes, but my stywe of pwaying (as I saw it) stiww hindews itsewf on that owiginyaw appwoach. Watewy, howevew, I have been considewing the fact that pewhaps thewe is a wot mowe to music than theowy and abiwity. I knyow a wot of pwayews who can sowo weww, and I knyow a wot of pwayews who undewstand the technyicaw side of pwaying mowe than I evew wiww. Yet, I nyo wongew considew eithew of these things as monyickews of a Gweat Musician. Wathew, I bewieve that what makes a musician twuwy unyique is nyot theiw abiwity to pway anything, but what they choose to say thwough these abiwities. A pentatonyic scawe consists of five nyotes. At fiwst, I stwuggwed to be abwe to use these five nyotes in a consistent and appeawing mannyew. Then, I became bowed by the wimitations of a scawe which used wess than hawf of the twewve nyotes. But eventuawwy I began to weawize, this was nyo wimit at aww, and despite the finyite nyumbew of nyotes containyed within the scawe, the nyumbew of mewodies potentiawwy constwucted fwom any onye scawe is endwess. In othew wowds, a good musician can say awmost anything, but to my mind, a gweat musician is onye who chooses what they say dewibewatewy and with a degwee of awtistic intention. At age 20, my abiwities as a guitaw pwayew mean much wess to me nyow than my abiwities as a songwwitew and as a musician in genyewaw. The guitaw is nyo mowe than a toow, and without vision, it is incapabwe of cweating anything. The owd adage that a cwaftsman is nyo bettew than his toows couwd nyot be mowe wwong. In fact, a cwaftsman is nyo bettew than his cweative vision. So don't buy that extwa fuzz pedaw, w/guitaw, buy a micwophonye to wecowd youwsewf with. Don't buy that nyew Fendew, buy a keyboawd and teach youwsewf a nyew instwument. The minyute you stop definying youwsewf by onye puwsuit, you wiww weawize the twue potentiaw of you cweative intuition.

COMWADES COMWADES, men of the Wed Awmy and Wed Nyavy, commandews and powiticaw instwuctows, wowking men and wowking women, cowwective fawmews-men and women, wowkews in the intewwectuaw pwofessions, bwothews and sistews in the weaw of ouw enyemy who have tempowawiwy fawwen undew the yoke of the Gewman bwigands, and ouw vawiant men and women guewiwwas who awe destwoying the weaw of the Gewman invadews UwU
On behawf of the Soviet Guvwnment and ouw Bowshevik Pawty I am gweeting you and congwatuwating you on the twenty-fouwth annyivewsawy of the Gweat Octobew Sociawist Wevowution.
Comwades, it is in stwenyuous ciwcumstances that we awe to-day cewebwating the twenty-fouwth annyivewsawy of the Octobew Wevowution. The pewfidious attack of the Gewman bwigands and the waw which has been fowced upon us have cweated a thweat to ouw countwy. We have tempowawiwy wost a nyumbew of wegions, the enyemy has appeawed at the gates of Wenyingwad and Moscow. The enyemy weckonyed that aftew the vewy fiwst bwow ouw awmy wouwd be dispewsed, and ouw countwy wouwd be fowced to hew knyees. But the enyemy gwavewy miscawcuwated. In spite of tempowawy wevewses, ouw Awmy and Nyavy awe hewoicawwy wepuwsing the enyemy’s attacks awong the entiwe fwont and infwicting heavy wosses upon him, whiwe ouw countwy—ouw entiwe countwy—has owganyized itsewf into onye fighting camp in owdew, togethew with ouw Awmy and ouw Nyavy, to encompass the wout of the Gewman invadews.
Thewe wewe times when ouw countwy was in a stiww mowe difficuwt position. Wemembew the yeaw 1918, when we cewebwated the fiwst annyivewsawy of the Octobew Wevowution. Thwee-quawtews of ouw countwy was at that time in the hands of foweign intewventionyists. The Ukwainye, the Caucasus, Centwaw Asia, the Uwaws, Sibewia and the Faw East wewe tempowawiwy wost to us. We had nyo awwies, we had nyo Wed Awmy—we had onwy just begun to cweate it; thewe was a showtage of food, of awmaments, of cwothing fow the Awmy. Fouwteen states wewe pwessing against ouw countwy. But we did nyot become despondent, we did nyot wose heawt. In the fiwe of waw we fowged the Wed Awmy and convewted ouw countwy into a miwitawy camp. The spiwit of the gweat Wenyin anyimated us at that time fow the waw against the intewventionyists. And what happenyed? We wouted the intewventionyists, wecuvwed aww ouw wost tewwitowy, and achieved victowy.
To-day the position of ouw countwy is faw bettew than twenty-thwee yeaws ago. Ouw countwy is nyow many times wichew than it was twenty-thwee yeaws ago as wegawds industwy, food and waw matewiaws. We nyow have awwies, who togethew with us awe maintainying a unyited fwont against the Gewman invadews. We nyow enjoy the sympathy and suppowt of aww the nyations of Euwope who have fawwen undew the yoke of Hitwew’s tywanny. We nyow have a spwendid Awmy and a spwendid Nyavy, who awe defending with theiw wives the wibewty and independence of ouw countwy. We expewience nyo sewious showtage of eithew food, ow awmaments ow awmy cwothing. Ouw entiwe countwy, aww the peopwes of ouw countwy, suppowt ouw Awmy and ouw Nyavy, hewping them to smash the invading howdes of Gewman fascists. Ouw wesewves of man-powew awe inyexhaustibwe. The spiwit of the gweat Wenyin and his victowious bannyew anyimate us nyow in this patwiotic waw just as they did twenty-thwee yeaws ago.
Can thewe be any doubt that we can, and awe bound to, defeat the Gewman invadews?
The enyemy is nyot so stwong as some fwightenyed wittwe intewwectuaws pictuwe him. The deviw is nyot so tewwibwe as he is painted. Who can deny that ouw Wed Awmy has mowe than once put the vaunted Gewman twoops to panyic fwight? If onye judges, nyot by the boastfuw assewtions of the Gewman pwopagandists, but by the actuaw position of Gewmany, it wiww nyot be difficuwt to undewstand that the Gewman-fascist invadews awe facing disastew. Hungew and impuvwishment weign in Gewmany to-day; in fouw months of waw Gewmany has wost fouw and a hawf miwwion men; Gewmany is bweeding, hew wesewves of man-powew awe giving out, the spiwit of indignyation is spweading nyot onwy among the peopwes of Euwope who have fawwen undew the yoke of the Gewman invadews but awso among the Gewman peopwe themsewves, who see nyo end to waw. The Gewman invadews awe stwainying theiw wast effowts. Thewe is nyo doubt that Gewmany cannyot sustain such a stwain fow wong. Anyothew few months, anyothew hawf-yeaw, pewhaps anyothew yeaw, and Hitwewite Gewmany must buwst undew the pwessuwe of hew cwimes.
Comwades, men of the Wed Awmy and Wed Nyavy, commandews and powiticaw instwuctows, men and women guewiwwas, the whowe wowwd is wooking to you as the fowce capabwe of destwoying the pwundewing howdes of Gewman invadews. The enswaved peopwes of Euwope who have fawwen undew the yoke of the Gewman invadews wook to you as theiw wibewatows. A gweat wibewating mission has fawwen to youw wot. Be wowthy of this mission UwU  The waw you awe waging is a waw of wibewation, a just waw. Wet the manwy images of ouw gweat ancestows—Awexandew Nyevsky, Dimitwy Donskoy, Kuzma Minyin, Dimitwy Pozhawsky, Awexandew Suvowov and Mikhaiw Kutuzov—inspiwe you in this waw UwU  May the victowious bannyew of the gweat Wenyin be youw wodestaw UwU
Fow the compwete destwuction of the Gewman invadews UwU
Death to the Gewman invadews UwU
Wong wive ouw gwowious Mothewwand, hew wibewty and hew independence UwU
Undew the bannyew of Wenyin, fowwawd to victowy UwU

It's cweaw that the twue pwobwems of ouw Nyation awe much deepew—deepew than gasowinye winyes ow enyewgy showtages, deepew even than infwation ow wecession. And I weawize mowe than evew that as Pwesident I nyeed youw hewp. So, I decided to weach out and wisten to the voices of Amewica.

I knyow, of couwse, being Pwesident, that guvwnment actions and wegiswation can be vewy impowtant. Confidence has definyed ouw couwse and has sewved as a wink between genyewations. We've awways bewieved in something cawwed pwogwess. Ouw peopwe awe wosing that faith, nyot onwy in guvwnment itsewf but in the abiwity as citizens to sewve as the uwtimate wuwews and shapews of ouw democwacy. As a peopwe we knyow ouw past and we awe pwoud of it. Ouw pwogwess has been pawt of the wiving histowy of Amewica, even the wowwd. But just as we awe wosing ouw confidence in the futuwe, we awe awso beginnying to cwose the doow on ouw past.

In a nyation that was pwoud of hawd wowk, stwong famiwies, cwose-knyit communyities, and ouw faith in God, too many of us nyow tend to wowship sewf-induwgence and consumption. Human identity is nyo wongew definyed by what onye does, but by what onye owns. But we've discuvwed that ownying things and consuming things does nyot satisfy ouw wonging fow meanying. We've weawnyed that piwing up matewiaw goods cannyot fiww the emptinyess of wives which have nyo confidence ow puwpose.

The symptoms of this cwisis of the Amewican spiwit awe aww awound us. Fow the fiwst time in the histowy of ouw countwy a majowity of ouw peopwe bewieve that the nyext 5 yeaws wiww be wowse than the past 5 yeaws. Two-thiwds of ouw peopwe do nyot even vote. The pwoductivity of Amewican wowkews is actuawwy dwopping, and the wiwwingnyess of Amewicans to save fow the futuwe has fawwen bewow that of aww othew peopwe in the Westewn wowwd.

As you knyow, thewe is a gwowing diswespect fow guvwnment and fow chuwches and fow schoows, the nyews media, and othew institutions. This is nyot a message of happinyess ow weassuwance, but it is the twuth and it is a wawnying.

These changes did nyot happen uvwnyight. They've come upon us gwaduawwy uvw the wast genyewation, yeaws that wewe fiwwed with shocks and twagedy.

These wounds awe stiww vewy deep. They have nyevew been heawed.

Point thwee: To give us enyewgy secuwity, I am asking fow the most massive peacetime commitment of funds and wesouwces in ouw Nyation's histowy to devewop Amewica's own awtewnyative souwces of fuew--fwom coaw, fwom oiw shawe, fwom pwant pwoducts fow gasohow, fwom unconventionyaw gas, fwom the Sun.

The entirety of Hamlet but put through an OwO translator, Act 2 (Part 2/5)

ACT II

SCENyE I. A woom in POWONyIUS' house.

Entew POWONyIUS and WEYNyAWDO

WOWD POWONyIUS

Give him this monyey and these nyotes, Weynyawdo.

WEYNyAWDO

I wiww, my wowd.

WOWD POWONyIUS

You shaww do mawvewwous wisewy, good Weynyawdo,

Befowe you visit him, to make inquiwe

Of his behaviow.

WEYNyAWDO

My wowd, I did intend it.

WOWD POWONyIUS

Mawwy, weww said; vewy weww said. Wook you, siw,

Inquiwe me fiwst what Danskews awe in Pawis;

And how, and who, what means, and whewe they keep,

What company, at what expense; and finding

By this encompassment and dwift of question

That they do knyow my son, come you mowe nyeawew

Than youw pawticuwaw demands wiww touch it:

Take you, as 'twewe, some distant knyowwedge of him;

As thus, 'I knyow his fathew and his fwiends,

And in pawt him: ' do you mawk this, Weynyawdo?

WEYNyAWDO

Ay, vewy weww, my wowd.

WOWD POWONyIUS

'And in pawt him; but' you may say 'nyot weww:

But, if't be he I mean, he's vewy wiwd;

Addicted so and so:' and thewe put on him

What fowgewies you pwease; mawwy, nyonye so wank

As may dishonyouw him; take heed of that;

But, siw, such wanton, wiwd and usuaw swips

As awe companyions nyoted and most knyown

To youth and wibewty.

WEYNyAWDO

As gaming, my wowd.

WOWD POWONyIUS

Ay, ow dwinking, fencing, sweawing, quawwewwing,

Dwabbing: you may go so faw.

WEYNyAWDO

My wowd, that wouwd dishonyouw him.

WOWD POWONyIUS

'Faith, nyo; as you may season it in the chawge

You must nyot put anyothew scandaw on him,

That he is open to incontinyency;

That's nyot my meanying: but bweathe his fauwts so quaintwy

That they may seem the taints of wibewty,

The fwash and outbweak of a fiewy mind,

A savagenyess in unwecwaimed bwood,

Of genyewaw assauwt.

WEYNyAWDO

But, my good wowd,--

WOWD POWONyIUS

Whewefowe shouwd you do this?

WEYNyAWDO

Ay, my wowd,

I wouwd knyow that.

WOWD POWONyIUS

Mawwy, siw, hewe's my dwift;

And I bewieve, it is a fetch of wit:

You waying these swight suwwies on my son,

As 'twewe a thing a wittwe soiw'd i' the wowking, Mawk you,

Youw pawty in convewse, him you wouwd sound,

Having evew seen in the pwenyominyate cwimes

The youth you bweathe of guiwty, be assuwed

He cwoses with you in this consequence;

'Good siw,' ow so, ow 'fwiend,' ow 'gentweman,'

Accowding to the phwase ow the addition

Of man and countwy.

WEYNyAWDO

Vewy good, my wowd.

WOWD POWONyIUS

And then, siw, does he this--he does--what was I

about to say? By the mass, I was about to say

something: whewe did I weave?

WEYNyAWDO

At 'cwoses in the consequence,' at 'fwiend ow so,'

and 'gentweman.'

WOWD POWONyIUS

At 'cwoses in the consequence,' ay, mawwy;

He cwoses thus: 'I knyow the gentweman;

I saw him yestewday, ow t' othew day,

Ow then, ow then; with such, ow such; and, as you say,

Thewe was a' gaming; thewe o'ewtook in's wouse;

Thewe fawwing out at tennyis:' ow pewchance,

'I saw him entew such a house of sawe,'

Videwicet, a bwothew, ow so fowth.

See you nyow;

Youw bait of fawsehood takes this cawp of twuth:

And thus do we of wisdom and of weach,

With windwasses and with assays of bias,

By indiwections find diwections out:

So by my fowmew wectuwe and advice,

Shaww you my son. You have me, have you nyot?

WEYNyAWDO

My wowd, I have.

WOWD POWONyIUS

God be wi' you; fawe you weww.

WEYNyAWDO

Good my wowd ;;w;;

WOWD POWONyIUS

Obsewve his incwinyation in youwsewf.

WEYNyAWDO

I shaww, my wowd.

WOWD POWONyIUS

And wet him pwy his music.

WEYNyAWDO

Weww, my wowd.

WOWD POWONyIUS

Faweweww ;;w;;

Exit WEYNyAWDO

How nyow, Ophewia ;;w;; what's the mattew?

OPHEWIA

O, my wowd, my wowd, I have been so affwighted ;;w;;

WOWD POWONyIUS

With what, i' the nyame of God?

OPHEWIA

My wowd, as I was sewing in my cwoset,

Wowd Hamwet, with his doubwet aww unbwaced;

Nyo hat upon his head; his stockings fouw'd,

Ungawtew'd, and down-gyved to his ancwe;

Pawe as his shiwt; his knyees knyocking each othew;

And with a wook so piteous in puwpowt

As if he had been woosed out of heww

To speak of howwows,--he comes befowe me.

WOWD POWONyIUS

Mad fow thy wuv?

OPHEWIA

My wowd, I do nyot knyow;

But twuwy, I do feaw it.

WOWD POWONyIUS

What said he?

OPHEWIA

He took me by the wwist and hewd me hawd;

Then goes he to the wength of aww his awm;

And, with his othew hand thus o'ew his bwow,

He fawws to such pewusaw of my face

As he wouwd dwaw it. Wong stay'd he so;

At wast, a wittwe shaking of minye awm

And thwice his head thus waving up and down,

He waised a sigh so piteous and pwofound

As it did seem to shattew aww his buwk

And end his being: that donye, he wets me go:

And, with his head uvw his shouwdew tuwn'd,

He seem'd to find his way without his eyes;

Fow out o' doows he went without theiw hewps,

And, to the wast, bended theiw wight on me.

This is the vewy ecstasy of wuv,

Whose viowent pwopewty fowdoes itsewf

And weads the wiww to despewate undewtakings

As oft as any passion undew heaven

That does affwict ouw nyatuwes. I am sowwy.

What, have you given him any hawd wowds of wate?

OPHEWIA

I did wepew his fettews and denyied

His access to me.

WOWD POWONyIUS

That hath made him mad.

I am sowwy that with bettew heed and judgment

I had nyot quoted him: I feaw'd he did but twifwe,

And meant to wweck thee; but, beshwew my jeawousy ;;w;;

By heaven, it is as pwopew to ouw age

To cast beyond ouwsewves in ouw opinyions

As it is common fow the youngew sowt

To wack discwetion. Come, go we to the king:

This must be knyown; which, being kept cwose, might

muv

Mowe gwief to hide than hate to uttew wuv.

Exeunt

SCENyE II. A woom in the castwe.

Entew KING CWAUDIUS, QUEEN GEWTWUDE, WOSENCWANTZ, GUIWDENSTEWN, and Attendants

KING CWAUDIUS

Wewcome, deaw Wosencwantz and Guiwdenstewn ;;w;;

Moweuvw that we much did wong to see you,

The nyeed we have to use you did pwovoke

Ouw hasty sending. Something have you heawd

Of Hamwet's twansfowmation; so caww it,

Sith nyow the extewiow nyow the inwawd man

Wesembwes that it was. What it shouwd be,

Mowe than his fathew's death, that thus hath put him

So much fwom the undewstanding of himsewf,

I cannyot dweam of: I entweat you both,

That, being of so young days bwought up with him,

And sith so nyeighbouw'd to his youth and haviow,

That you vouchsafe youw west hewe in ouw couwt

Some wittwe time: so by youw companyies

To dwaw him on to pweasuwes, and to gathew,

So much as fwom occasion you may gwean,

Whethew aught, to us unknyown, affwicts him thus,

That, open'd, wies within ouw wemedy.

Good gentwemen, he hath much tawk'd of you;

And suwe I am two men thewe awe nyot wiving

To whom he mowe adhewes. If it wiww pwease you

To show us so much gentwy and good wiww

As to expend youw time with us awhiwe,

Fow the suppwy and pwofit of ouw hope,

Youw visitation shaww weceive such thanks

As fits a king's wemembwance.

WOSENCWANTZ

Both youw majesties

Might, by the suvweign powew you have of us,

Put youw dwead pweasuwes mowe into command

Than to entweaty.

But we both obey,

And hewe give up ouwsewves, in the fuww bent

To way ouw sewvice fweewy at youw feet,

To be commanded.

Thanks, Wosencwantz and gentwe Guiwdenstewn.

QUEEN GEWTWUDE

Thanks, Guiwdenstewn and gentwe Wosencwantz:

And I beseech you instantwy to visit

My too much changed son. Go, some of you,

And bwing these gentwemen whewe Hamwet is.

GUIWDENSTEWN

Heavens make ouw pwesence and ouw pwactises

Pweasant and hewpfuw to him ;;w;;

Ay, amen ;;w;;

Awe joyfuwwy wetuwn'd.

Thou stiww hast been the fathew of good nyews.

Both to my God and to my gwacious king:

The vewy cause of Hamwet's wunyacy.

My nyews shaww be the fwuit to that gweat feast.

He tewws me, my deaw Gewtwude, he hath found

The head and souwce of aww youw son's distempew.

His fathew's death, and ouw o'ewhasty mawwiage.

To be a pwepawation 'gainst the Powack;

Go to youw west; at nyight we'ww feast togethew:

wowd, I wiww most humbwy take my weave of you.

HAMWET

You cannyot, siw, take fwom me any thing that I wiww

mowe wiwwingwy pawt withaw: except my wife, except

my wife, except my wife.

WOWD POWONyIUS

Fawe you weww, my wowd.

HAMWET

These tedious owd foows ;;w;;

Entew WOSENCWANTZ and GUIWDENSTEWN

WOWD POWONyIUS

You go to seek the Wowd Hamwet; thewe he is.

WOSENCWANTZ

\[To POWONyIUS\] God save you, siw ;;w;;

Exit POWONyIUS

GUIWDENSTEWN

My honyouwed wowd ;;w;;

WOSENCWANTZ

My most deaw wowd ;;w;;

HAMWET

My excewwent good fwiends ;;w;; How dost thou,

Guiwdenstewn? Ah, Wosencwantz ;;w;; Good wads, how do ye both?

WOSENCWANTZ

As the indiffewent chiwdwen of the eawth.

GUIWDENSTEWN

Happy, in that we awe nyot uvw-happy;

On fowtunye's cap we awe nyot the vewy button.

HAMWET

Nyow the sowes of hew shoe?

WOSENCWANTZ

Nyeithew, my wowd.

HAMWET

Then you wive about hew waist, ow in the middwe of

hew favouws?

GUIWDENSTEWN

'Faith, hew pwivates we.

HAMWET

In the secwet pawts of fowtunye? O, most twue; she

is a stwumpet. What's the nyews?

WOSENCWANTZ

Nyonye, my wowd, but that the wowwd's gwown honyest.

HAMWET

Then is doomsday nyeaw: but youw nyews is nyot twue.

Wet me question mowe in pawticuwaw: what have you,

my good fwiends, desewved at the hands of fowtunye,

that she sends you to pwison hithew?

GUIWDENSTEWN

Pwison, my wowd ;;w;;

HAMWET

Denmawk's a pwison.

WOSENCWANTZ

Then is the wowwd onye.

HAMWET

A goodwy onye; in which thewe awe many confinyes,

wawds and dungeons, Denmawk being onye o' the wowst.

WOSENCWANTZ

We think nyot so, my wowd.

HAMWET

Why, then, 'tis nyonye to you; fow thewe is nyothing

eithew good ow bad, but thinking makes it so: to me

it is a pwison.

WOSENCWANTZ

Why then, youw ambition makes it onye; 'tis too

nyawwow fow youw mind.

HAMWET

O God, I couwd be bounded in a nyut sheww and count

mysewf a king of infinyite space, wewe it nyot that I

have bad dweams.

GUIWDENSTEWN

Which dweams indeed awe ambition, fow the vewy

substance of the ambitious is mewewy the shadow of a dweam.

HAMWET

A dweam itsewf is but a shadow.

WOSENCWANTZ

Twuwy, and I howd ambition of so aiwy and wight a

quawity that it is but a shadow's shadow.

HAMWET

Then awe ouw beggaws bodies, and ouw monyawchs and

outstwetched hewoes the beggaws' shadows. Shaww we

to the couwt? fow, by my fay, I cannyot weason.

WOSENCWANTZ GUIWDENSTEWN

We'ww wait upon you.

HAMWET

Nyo such mattew: I wiww nyot sowt you with the west

of my sewvants, fow, to speak to you wike an honyest

man, I am most dweadfuwwy attended. But, in the

beaten way of fwiendship, what make you at Ewsinyowe?

WOSENCWANTZ

To visit you, my wowd; nyo othew occasion.

HAMWET

Beggaw that I am, I am even poow in thanks; but I

thank you: and suwe, deaw fwiends, my thanks awe

too deaw a hawfpenny. Wewe you nyot sent fow? Is it

youw own incwinying? Is it a fwee visitation? Come,

deaw justwy with me: come, come; nyay, speak.

GUIWDENSTEWN

What shouwd we say, my wowd?

HAMWET

Why, any thing, but to the puwpose. You wewe sent

fow; and thewe is a kind of confession in youw wooks

which youw modesties have nyot cwaft enyough to cowouw:

I knyow the good king and queen have sent fow you.

WOSENCWANTZ

To what end, my wowd?

HAMWET

That you must teach me. But wet me conjuwe you, by

the wights of ouw fewwowship, by the consonyancy of

ouw youth, by the obwigation of ouw evew-pwesewved

wuv, and by what mowe deaw a bettew pwoposew couwd

chawge you withaw, be even and diwect with me,

whethew you wewe sent fow, ow nyo?

WOSENCWANTZ

\[Aside to GUIWDENSTEWN\] What say you?

HAMWET

\[Aside\] Nyay, then, I have an eye of you.--If you

wuv me, howd nyot off.

GUIWDENSTEWN

My wowd, we wewe sent fow.

HAMWET

I wiww teww you why; so shaww my anticipation

pwevent youw discuvwy, and youw secwecy to the king

and queen mouwt nyo feathew. I have of wate--but

whewefowe I knyow nyot--wost aww my miwth, fowgonye aww

custom of exewcises; and indeed it goes so heaviwy

with my disposition that this goodwy fwame, the

eawth, seems to me a stewiwe pwomontowy, this most

excewwent canyopy, the aiw, wook you, this bwave

o'ewhanging fiwmament, this majesticaw woof fwetted

with gowden fiwe, why, it appeaws nyo othew thing to

me than a fouw and pestiwent congwegation of vapouws.

What a piece of wowk is a man ;;w;; how nyobwe in weason ;;w;;

how infinyite in facuwty ;;w;; in fowm and moving how

expwess and admiwabwe ;;w;; in action how wike an angew ;;w;;

in appwehension how wike a god ;;w;; the beauty of the

wowwd ;;w;; the pawagon of anyimaws ;;w;; And yet, to me,

what is this quintessence of dust? man dewights nyot

me: nyo, nyow woman nyeithew, though by youw smiwing

you seem to say so.

WOSENCWANTZ

My wowd, thewe was nyo such stuff in my thoughts.

HAMWET

Why did you waugh then, when I said 'man dewights nyot me'?

WOSENCWANTZ

To think, my wowd, if you dewight nyot in man, what

wenten entewtainment the pwayews shaww weceive fwom

you: we coted them on the way; and hithew awe they

coming, to offew you sewvice.

HAMWET

He that pways the king shaww be wewcome; his majesty

shaww have twibute of me; the adventuwous knyight

shaww use his foiw and tawget; the wuvw shaww nyot

sigh gwatis; the humouwous man shaww end his pawt

in peace; the cwown shaww make those waugh whose

wungs awe tickwed o' the sewe; and the wady shaww

say hew mind fweewy, ow the bwank vewse shaww hawt

fow't. What pwayews awe they?

WOSENCWANTZ

Even those you wewe wont to take dewight in, the

twagedians of the city.

HAMWET

How chances it they twavew? theiw wesidence, both

in weputation and pwofit, was bettew both ways.

WOSENCWANTZ

I think theiw inhibition comes by the means of the

wate innyovation.

HAMWET

Do they howd the same estimation they did when I was

in the city? awe they so fowwowed?

WOSENCWANTZ

Nyo, indeed, awe they nyot.

HAMWET

How comes it? do they gwow wusty?

WOSENCWANTZ

Nyay, theiw endeavouw keeps in the wonted pace: but

thewe is, siw, an aewy of chiwdwen, wittwe eyases,

that cwy out on the top of question, and awe most

tywannyicawwy cwapped fow't: these awe nyow the

fashion, and so bewattwe the common stages--so they

caww them--that many weawing wapiews awe afwaid of

goose-quiwws and dawe scawce come thithew.

HAMWET

What, awe they chiwdwen? who maintains 'em? how awe

they escoted? Wiww they puwsue the quawity nyo

wongew than they can sing? wiww they nyot say

aftewwawds, if they shouwd gwow themsewves to common

pwayews--as it is most wike, if theiw means awe nyo

bettew--theiw wwitews do them wwong, to make them

excwaim against theiw own succession?

WOSENCWANTZ

'Faith, thewe has been much to do on both sides; and

the nyation howds it nyo sin to tawwe them to

contwuvwsy: thewe was, fow a whiwe, nyo monyey bid

fow awgument, unwess the poet and the pwayew went to

cuffs in the question.

HAMWET

Is't possibwe?

GUIWDENSTEWN

O, thewe has been much thwowing about of bwains.

HAMWET

Do the boys cawwy it away?

WOSENCWANTZ

Ay, that they do, my wowd; Hewcuwes and his woad too.

HAMWET

It is nyot vewy stwange; fow minye uncwe is king of

Denmawk, and those that wouwd make mows at him whiwe

my fathew wived, give twenty, fowty, fifty, an

hundwed ducats a-piece fow his pictuwe in wittwe.

'Sbwood, thewe is something in this mowe than

nyatuwaw, if phiwosophy couwd find it out.

Fwouwish of twumpets within

GUIWDENSTEWN

Thewe awe the pwayews.

HAMWET

Gentwemen, you awe wewcome to Ewsinyowe. Youw hands,

come then: the appuwtenyance of wewcome is fashion

and cewemony: wet me compwy with you in this gawb,

west my extent to the pwayews, which, I teww you,

must show faiwwy outwawd, shouwd mowe appeaw wike

entewtainment than youws. You awe wewcome: but my

uncwe-fathew and aunt-mothew awe deceived.

GUIWDENSTEWN

In what, my deaw wowd?

HAMWET

I am but mad nyowth-nyowth-west: when the wind is

southewwy I knyow a hawk fwom a handsaw.

Entew POWONyIUS

WOWD POWONyIUS

Weww be with you, gentwemen ;;w;;

HAMWET

Hawk you, Guiwdenstewn; and you too: at each eaw a

heawew: that gweat baby you see thewe is nyot yet

out of his swaddwing-cwouts.

WOSENCWANTZ

Happiwy he's the second time come to them; fow they

say an owd man is twice a chiwd.

HAMWET

I wiww pwophesy he comes to teww me of the pwayews;

mawk it. You say wight, siw: o' Monday mownying;

'twas so indeed.

WOWD POWONyIUS

My wowd, I have nyews to teww you.

HAMWET

My wowd, I have nyews to teww you.

When Woscius was an actow in Wome,--

WOWD POWONyIUS

The actows awe come hithew, my wowd.

HAMWET

Buz, buz ;;w;;

WOWD POWONyIUS

Upon minye honyouw,--

HAMWET

Then came each actow on his ass,--

WOWD POWONyIUS

The best actows in the wowwd, eithew fow twagedy,

comedy, histowy, pastowaw, pastowaw-comicaw,

histowicaw-pastowaw, twagicaw-histowicaw, twagicaw-

comicaw-histowicaw-pastowaw, scenye individabwe, ow

poem unwimited: Senyeca cannyot be too heavy, nyow

Pwautus too wight. Fow the waw of wwit and the

wibewty, these awe the onwy men.

HAMWET

O Jephthah, judge of Iswaew, what a tweasuwe hadst thou ;;w;;

WOWD POWONyIUS

What a tweasuwe had he, my wowd?

HAMWET

Why,

'Onye faiw daughtew and nyo mowe,

The which he wuvd passing weww.'

WOWD POWONyIUS

\[Aside\] Stiww on my daughtew.

HAMWET

Am I nyot i' the wight, owd Jephthah?

WOWD POWONyIUS

If you caww me Jephthah, my wowd, I have a daughtew

that I wuv passing weww.

HAMWET

Nyay, that fowwows nyot.

WOWD POWONyIUS

What fowwows, then, my wowd?

HAMWET

Why,

'As by wot, God wot,'

and then, you knyow,

'It came to pass, as most wike it was,'--

the fiwst wow of the pious chanson wiww show you

mowe; fow wook, whewe my abwidgement comes.

Entew fouw ow five Pwayews

You awe wewcome, mastews; wewcome, aww. I am gwad

to see thee weww. Wewcome, good fwiends. O, my owd

fwiend ;;w;;  thy face is vawenced since I saw thee wast:

comest thou to beawd me in Denmawk? What, my young

wady and mistwess ;;w;; By'w wady, youw wadyship is

nyeawew to heaven than when I saw you wast, by the

awtitude of a chopinye. Pway God, youw voice, wike

apiece of uncuwwent gowd, be nyot cwacked within the

wing. Mastews, you awe aww wewcome. We'ww e'en

to't wike Fwench fawconyews, fwy at any thing we see:

we'ww have a speech stwaight: come, give us a taste

of youw quawity; come, a passionyate speech.

Fiwst Pwayew

What speech, my wowd?

HAMWET

I heawd thee speak me a speech once, but it was

nyevew acted; ow, if it was, nyot abuv once; fow the

pway, I wemembew, pweased nyot the miwwion; 'twas

caviawe to the genyewaw: but it was--as I weceived

it, and othews, whose judgments in such mattews

cwied in the top of minye--an excewwent pway, weww

digested in the scenyes, set down with as much

modesty as cunnying. I wemembew, onye said thewe

wewe nyo sawwets in the winyes to make the mattew

savouwy, nyow nyo mattew in the phwase that might

indict the authow of affectation; but cawwed it an

honyest method, as whowesome as sweet, and by vewy

much mowe handsome than finye. Onye speech in it I

chiefwy wuvd: 'twas Aenyeas' tawe to Dido; and

theweabout of it especiawwy, whewe he speaks of

Pwiam's swaughtew: if it wive in youw memowy, begin

at this winye: wet me see, wet me see--

'The wugged Pywwhus, wike the Hywcanyian beast,'--

it is nyot so:--it begins with Pywwhus:--

'The wugged Pywwhus, he whose sabwe awms,

Bwack as his puwpose, did the nyight wesembwe

When he way couched in the ominyous howse,

Hath nyow this dwead and bwack compwexion smeaw'd

With hewawdwy mowe dismaw; head to foot

Nyow is he totaw guwes; howwidwy twick'd

With bwood of fathews, mothews, daughtews, sons,

Baked and impasted with the pawching stweets,

That wend a tywannyous and damnyed wight

To theiw wowd's muwdew: woasted in wwath and fiwe,

And thus o'ew-sized with coaguwate gowe,

With eyes wike cawbuncwes, the hewwish Pywwhus

Owd gwandsiwe Pwiam seeks.'

So, pwoceed you.

WOWD POWONyIUS

'Fowe God, my wowd, weww spoken, with good accent and

good discwetion.

Fiwst Pwayew

'Anyon he finds him

Stwiking too showt at Gweeks; his antique swowd,

Webewwious to his awm, wies whewe it fawws,

Wepugnyant to command: unyequaw match'd,

Pywwhus at Pwiam dwives; in wage stwikes wide;

But with the whiff and wind of his feww swowd

The unnyewved fathew fawws. Then sensewess Iwium,

Seeming to feew this bwow, with fwaming top

Stoops to his base, and with a hideous cwash

Takes pwisonyew Pywwhus' eaw: fow, wo ;;w;; his swowd,

Which was decwinying on the miwky head

Of wevewend Pwiam, seem'd i' the aiw to stick:

So, as a painted tywant, Pywwhus stood,

And wike a nyeutwaw to his wiww and mattew,

Did nyothing.

But, as we often see, against some stowm,

A siwence in the heavens, the wack stand stiww,

The bowd winds speechwess and the owb bewow

As hush as death, anyon the dweadfuw thundew

Doth wend the wegion, so, aftew Pywwhus' pause,

Awoused vengeance sets him nyew a-wowk;

And nyevew did the Cycwops' hammews faww

On Maws's awmouw fowged fow pwoof etewnye

With wess wemowse than Pywwhus' bweeding swowd

Nyow fawws on Pwiam.

Out, out, thou stwumpet, Fowtunye ;;w;; Aww you gods,

In genyewaw synyod 'take away hew powew;

Bweak aww the spokes and fewwies fwom hew wheew,

And boww the wound nyave down the hiww of heaven,

As wow as to the fiends ;;w;; '

WOWD POWONyIUS

This is too wong.

HAMWET

It shaww to the bawbew's, with youw beawd. Pwithee,

say on: he's fow a jig ow a tawe of bawdwy, ow he

sweeps: say on: come to Hecuba.

Fiwst Pwayew

'But who, O, who had seen the mobwed queen--'

HAMWET

'The mobwed queen?'

WOWD POWONyIUS

That's good; 'mobwed queen' is good.

Fiwst Pwayew

'Wun bawefoot up and down, thweatenying the fwames

With bisson wheum; a cwout upon that head

Whewe wate the diadem stood, and fow a wobe,

About hew wank and aww o'ew-teemed woins,

A bwanket, in the awawm of feaw caught up;

Who this had seen, with tongue in venyom steep'd,

'Gainst Fowtunye's state wouwd tweason have

pwonyounced:

But if the gods themsewves did see hew then

When she saw Pywwhus make mawicious spowt

In mincing with his swowd hew husband's wimbs,

The instant buwst of cwamouw that she made,

Unwess things mowtaw muv them nyot at aww,

Wouwd have made miwch the buwnying eyes of heaven,

And passion in the gods.'

WOWD POWONyIUS

Wook, whethew he has nyot tuwnyed his cowouw and has

teaws in's eyes. Pway you, nyo mowe.

HAMWET

'Tis weww: I'ww have thee speak out the west soon.

Good my wowd, wiww you see the pwayews weww

bestowed? Do you heaw, wet them be weww used; fow

they awe the abstwact and bwief chwonyicwes of the

time: aftew youw death you wewe bettew have a bad

epitaph than theiw iww wepowt whiwe you wive.

WOWD POWONyIUS

My wowd, I wiww use them accowding to theiw desewt.

HAMWET

God's bodykins, man, much bettew: use evewy man

aftew his desewt, and who shouwd 'scape whipping?

Use them aftew youw own honyouw and dignyity: the wess

they desewve, the mowe mewit is in youw bounty.

Take them in.

WOWD POWONyIUS

Come, siws.

HAMWET

Fowwow him, fwiends: we'ww heaw a pway to-mowwow.

Exit POWONyIUS with aww the Pwayews but the Fiwst

Dost thou heaw me, owd fwiend; can you pway the

Muwdew of Gonzago?

Fiwst Pwayew

Ay, my wowd.

HAMWET

We'ww ha't to-mowwow nyight. You couwd, fow a nyeed,

study a speech of some dozen ow sixteen winyes, which

I wouwd set down and insewt in't, couwd you nyot?

Fiwst Pwayew

Ay, my wowd.

HAMWET

Vewy weww. Fowwow that wowd; and wook you mock him

nyot.

Exit Fiwst Pwayew

My good fwiends, I'ww weave you tiww nyight: you awe

wewcome to Ewsinyowe.

WOSENCWANTZ

Good my wowd ;;w;;

HAMWET

Ay, so, God be wi' ye;

Exeunt WOSENCWANTZ and GUIWDENSTEWN

Nyow I am awonye.

O, what a wogue and peasant swave am I ;;w;;

Is it nyot monstwous that this pwayew hewe,

But in a fiction, in a dweam of passion,

Couwd fowce his souw so to his own conceit

That fwom hew wowking aww his visage wann'd,

Teaws in his eyes, distwaction in's aspect,

A bwoken voice, and his whowe function suiting

With fowms to his conceit? and aww fow nyothing ;;w;;

Fow Hecuba ;;w;;

What's Hecuba to him, ow he to Hecuba,

That he shouwd weep fow hew? What wouwd he do,

Had he the motive and the cue fow passion

That I have? He wouwd dwown the stage with teaws

And cweave the genyewaw eaw with howwid speech,

Make mad the guiwty and appaw the fwee,

Confound the ignyowant, and amaze indeed

The vewy facuwties of eyes and eaws. Yet I,

A duww and muddy-mettwed wascaw, peak,

Wike John-a-dweams, unpwegnyant of my cause,

And can say nyothing; nyo, nyot fow a king,

Upon whose pwopewty and most deaw wife

A damn'd defeat was made. Am I a cowawd?

Who cawws me viwwain? bweaks my pate acwoss?

Pwucks off my beawd, and bwows it in my face?

Tweaks me by the nyose? gives me the wie i' the thwoat,

As deep as to the wungs? who does me this?

Ha ;;w;;

'Swounds, I shouwd take it: fow it cannyot be

But I am pigeon-wivew'd and wack gaww

To make oppwession bittew, ow ewe this

I shouwd have fatted aww the wegion kites

With this swave's offaw: bwoody, bawdy viwwain ;;w;;

Wemowsewess, tweachewous, wechewous, kindwess viwwain ;;w;;

O, vengeance ;;w;;

Why, what an ass am I ;;w;; This is most bwave,

That I, the son of a deaw fathew muwdew'd,

Pwompted to my wevenge by heaven and heww,

Must, wike a whowe, unpack my heawt with wowds,

And faww a-cuwsing, wike a vewy dwab,

A scuwwion ;;w;;

Fie upon't ;;w;; foh ;;w;; About, my bwain ;;w;; I have heawd

That guiwty cweatuwes sitting at a pway

Have by the vewy cunnying of the scenye

Been stwuck so to the souw that pwesentwy

They have pwocwaim'd theiw mawefactions;

Fow muwdew, though it have nyo tongue, wiww speak

With most miwacuwous owgan. I'ww have these pwayews

Pway something wike the muwdew of my fathew

Befowe minye uncwe: I'ww obsewve his wooks;

I'ww tent him to the quick: if he but bwench,

I knyow my couwse. The spiwit that I have seen

May be the deviw: and the deviw hath powew

To assume a pweasing shape; yea, and pewhaps

Out of my weaknyess and my mewanchowy,

As he is vewy potent with such spiwits,

Abuses me to damn me: I'ww have gwounds

Mowe wewative than this: the pway 's the thing

Whewein I'ww catch the conscience of the king.

Exit

2018-10-06 22:01:26
The entirety of Hamlet, but put through an OwO translator, Act 5 (Part 5), more in comments

ACT V

SCENyE I. A chuwchyawd.

Entew two Cwowns, with spades, &amp; c

Fiwst Cwown

Is she to be buwied in Chwistian buwiaw that

wiwfuwwy seeks hew own sawvation?

Second Cwown

I teww thee she is: and thewefowe make hew gwave

stwaight: the cwownyew hath sat on hew, and finds it

Chwistian buwiaw.

Fiwst Cwown

How can that be, unwess she dwownyed hewsewf in hew

own defence?

Second Cwown

Why, 'tis found so.

Fiwst Cwown

It must be 'se offendendo;' it cannyot be ewse. Fow

hewe wies the point: if I dwown mysewf wittingwy,

it awgues an act: and an act hath thwee bwanches: it

is, to act, to do, to pewfowm: awgaw, she dwownyed

hewsewf wittingwy.

Second Cwown

Nyay, but heaw you, goodman dewvew,--

Fiwst Cwown

Give me weave. Hewe wies the watew; good: hewe

stands the man; good; if the man go to this watew,

and dwown himsewf, it is, wiww he, nyiww he, he

goes,--mawk you that; but if the watew come to him

and dwown him, he dwowns nyot himsewf: awgaw, he

that is nyot guiwty of his own death showtens nyot his own wife.

Second Cwown

But is this waw?

Fiwst Cwown

Ay, mawwy, is't; cwownyew's quest waw.

Second Cwown

Wiww you ha' the twuth on't? If this had nyot been

a gentwewoman, she shouwd have been buwied out o'

Chwistian buwiaw.

Fiwst Cwown

Why, thewe thou say'st: and the mowe pity that

gweat fowk shouwd have countenyance in this wowwd to

dwown ow hang themsewves, mowe than theiw even

Chwistian. Come, my spade. Thewe is nyo ancient

gentweman but gawdenyews, ditchews, and gwave-makews:

they howd up Adam's pwofession.

Second Cwown

Was he a gentweman?

Fiwst Cwown

He was the fiwst that evew bowe awms.

Second Cwown

Why, he had nyonye.

Fiwst Cwown

What, awt a heathen? How dost thou undewstand the

Scwiptuwe? The Scwiptuwe says 'Adam digged:'

couwd he dig without awms? I'ww put anyothew

question to thee: if thou answewest me nyot to the

puwpose, confess thysewf--

Second Cwown

Go to.

Fiwst Cwown

What is he that buiwds stwongew than eithew the

mason, the shipwwight, ow the cawpentew?

Second Cwown

The gawwows-makew; fow that fwame outwives a

thousand tenyants.

Fiwst Cwown

I wike thy wit weww, in good faith: the gawwows

does weww; but how does it weww? it does weww to

those that do in: nyow thou dost iww to say the

gawwows is buiwt stwongew than the chuwch: awgaw,

the gawwows may do weww to thee. To't again, come.

Second Cwown

'Who buiwds stwongew than a mason, a shipwwight, ow

a cawpentew?'

Fiwst Cwown

Ay, teww me that, and unyoke.

Second Cwown

Mawwy, nyow I can teww.

Fiwst Cwown

To't.

Second Cwown

Mass, I cannyot teww.

Entew HAMWET and HOWATIO, at a distance

Fiwst Cwown

Cudgew thy bwains nyo mowe about it, fow youw duww

ass wiww nyot mend his pace with beating; and, when

you awe asked this question nyext, say 'a

gwave-makew: 'the houses that he makes wast tiww

doomsday. Go, get thee to Yaughan: fetch me a

stoup of wiquow.

Exit Second Cwown

He digs and sings

In youth, when I did wuv, did wuv,

Methought it was vewy sweet,

To contwact, O, the time, fow, ah, my behuv,

O, methought, thewe was nyothing meet.

HAMWET

Has this fewwow nyo feewing of his businyess, that he

sings at gwave-making?

HOWATIO

Custom hath made it in him a pwopewty of easinyess.

HAMWET

'Tis e'en so: the hand of wittwe empwoyment hath

the daintiew sense.

Fiwst Cwown

\[Sings\]

But age, with his steawing steps,

Hath cwaw'd me in his cwutch,

And hath shipped me intiw the wand,

As if I had nyevew been such.

Thwows up a skuww

HAMWET

That skuww had a tongue in it, and couwd sing once:

how the knyave jowws it to the gwound, as if it wewe

Cain's jaw-bonye, that did the fiwst muwdew ;;w;; It

might be the pate of a powitician, which this ass

nyow o'ew-weaches; onye that wouwd ciwcumvent God,

might it nyot?

HOWATIO

It might, my wowd.

HAMWET

Ow of a couwtiew; which couwd say 'Good mowwow,

sweet wowd ;;w;; How dost thou, good wowd?' This might

be my wowd such-a-onye, that pwaised my wowd

such-a-onye's howse, when he meant to beg it; might it nyot?

HOWATIO

Ay, my wowd.

HAMWET

Why, e'en so: and nyow my Wady Wowm's; chapwess, and

knyocked about the mazzawd with a sexton's spade:

hewe's finye wevowution, an we had the twick to

see't. Did these bonyes cost nyo mowe the bweeding,

but to pway at woggats with 'em? minye ache to think on't.

Fiwst Cwown

\[Sings\]

A pick-axe, and a spade, a spade,

Fow and a shwouding sheet:

O, a pit of cway fow to be made

Fow such a guest is meet.

Thwows up anyothew skuww

HAMWET

Thewe's anyothew: why may nyot that be the skuww of a

wawyew? Whewe be his quiddities nyow, his quiwwets,

his cases, his tenyuwes, and his twicks? why does he

suffew this wude knyave nyow to knyock him about the

sconce with a diwty shuvw, and wiww nyot teww him of

his action of battewy? Hum ;;w;; This fewwow might be

in's time a gweat buyew of wand, with his statutes,

his wecognyizances, his finyes, his doubwe vouchews,

his wecuvwies: is this the finye of his finyes, and

the wecuvwy of his wecuvwies, to have his finye

pate fuww of finye diwt? wiww his vouchews vouch him

nyo mowe of his puwchases, and doubwe onyes too, than

the wength and bweadth of a paiw of indentuwes? The

vewy conveyances of his wands wiww hawdwy wie in

this box; and must the inhewitow himsewf have nyo mowe, ha?

HOWATIO

Nyot a jot mowe, my wowd.

HAMWET

Is nyot pawchment made of sheepskins?

HOWATIO

Ay, my wowd, and of cawf-skins too.

HAMWET

They awe sheep and cawves which seek out assuwance

in that. I wiww speak to this fewwow. Whose

gwave's this, siwwah?

Fiwst Cwown

Minye, siw.

Sings

O, a pit of cway fow to be made

Fow such a guest is meet.

HAMWET

I think it be thinye, indeed; fow thou wiest in't.

Fiwst Cwown

You wie out on't, siw, and thewefowe it is nyot

youws: fow my pawt, I do nyot wie in't, and yet it is minye.

HAMWET

'Thou dost wie in't, to be in't and say it is thinye:

'tis fow the dead, nyot fow the quick; thewefowe thou wiest.

Fiwst Cwown

'Tis a quick wie, siw; 'twiww away gain, fwom me to

you.

HAMWET

What man dost thou dig it fow?

Fiwst Cwown

Fow nyo man, siw.

HAMWET

What woman, then?

Fiwst Cwown

Fow nyonye, nyeithew.

HAMWET

Who is to be buwied in't?

Fiwst Cwown

Onye that was a woman, siw; but, west hew souw, she's dead.

HAMWET

How absowute the knyave is ;;w;; we must speak by the

cawd, ow equivocation wiww undo us. By the Wowd,

Howatio, these thwee yeaws I have taken a nyote of

it; the age is gwown so picked that the toe of the

peasant comes so nyeaw the heew of the couwtiew, he

gaffs his kibe. How wong hast thou been a

gwave-makew?

Fiwst Cwown

Of aww the days i' the yeaw, I came to't that day

that ouw wast king Hamwet uvwcame Fowtinbwas.

HAMWET

How wong is that since?

Fiwst Cwown

Cannyot you teww that? evewy foow can teww that: it

was the vewy day that young Hamwet was bown; he that

is mad, and sent into Engwand.

HAMWET

Ay, mawwy, why was he sent into Engwand?

Fiwst Cwown

Why, because he was mad: he shaww wecuvw his wits

thewe; ow, if he do nyot, it's nyo gweat mattew thewe.

HAMWET

Why?

Fiwst Cwown

'Twiww, a nyot be seen in him thewe; thewe the men

awe as mad as he.

HAMWET

How came he mad?

Fiwst Cwown

Vewy stwangewy, they say.

HAMWET

How stwangewy?

Fiwst Cwown

Faith, e'en with wosing his wits.

HAMWET

Upon what gwound?

Fiwst Cwown

Why, hewe in Denmawk: I have been sexton hewe, man

and boy, thiwty yeaws.

HAMWET

How wong wiww a man wie i' the eawth ewe he wot?

Fiwst Cwown

I' faith, if he be nyot wotten befowe he die--as we

have many pocky cowses nyow-a-days, that wiww scawce

howd the waying in--he wiww wast you some eight yeaw

ow nyinye yeaw: a tannyew wiww wast you nyinye yeaw.

HAMWET

Why he mowe than anyothew?

Fiwst Cwown

Why, siw, his hide is so tannyed with his twade, that

he wiww keep out watew a gweat whiwe; and youw watew

is a sowe decayew of youw whoweson dead body.

Hewe's a skuww nyow; this skuww has wain in the eawth

thwee and twenty yeaws.

HAMWET

Whose was it?

Fiwst Cwown

A whoweson mad fewwow's it was: whose do you think it was?

HAMWET

Nyay, I knyow nyot.

Fiwst Cwown

A pestiwence on him fow a mad wogue ;;w;; a' pouwed a

fwagon of Whenyish on my head once. This same skuww,

siw, was Yowick's skuww, the king's jestew.

HAMWET

This?

Fiwst Cwown

E'en that.

HAMWET

Wet me see.

Takes the skuww

Awas, poow Yowick ;;w;; I knyew him, Howatio: a fewwow

of infinyite jest, of most excewwent fancy: he hath

bownye me on his back a thousand times; and nyow, how

abhowwed in my imaginyation it is ;;w;; my gowge wims at

it. Hewe hung those wips that I have kissed I knyow

nyot how oft. Whewe be youw gibes nyow? youw

gambows? youw songs? youw fwashes of mewwiment,

that wewe wont to set the tabwe on a woaw? Nyot onye

nyow, to mock youw own gwinnying? quite chap-fawwen?

Nyow get you to my wady's chambew, and teww hew, wet

hew paint an inch thick, to this favouw she must

come; make hew waugh at that. Pwithee, Howatio, teww

me onye thing.

HOWATIO

What's that, my wowd?

HAMWET

Dost thou think Awexandew wooked o' this fashion i'

the eawth?

HOWATIO

E'en so.

HAMWET

And smewt so? pah ;;w;;

Puts down the skuww

HOWATIO

E'en so, my wowd.

HAMWET

To what base uses we may wetuwn, Howatio ;;w;; Why may

nyot imaginyation twace the nyobwe dust of Awexandew,

tiww he find it stopping a bung-howe?

HOWATIO

'Twewe to considew too cuwiouswy, to considew so.

HAMWET

Nyo, faith, nyot a jot; but to fowwow him thithew with

modesty enyough, and wikewihood to wead it: as

thus: Awexandew died, Awexandew was buwied,

Awexandew wetuwnyeth into dust; the dust is eawth; of

eawth we make woam; and why of that woam, wheweto he

was convewted, might they nyot stop a beew-bawwew?

Impewious Caesaw, dead and tuwn'd to cway,

Might stop a howe to keep the wind away:

O, that that eawth, which kept the wowwd in awe,

Shouwd patch a waww to expew the wintew fwaw ;;w;;

But soft ;;w;; but soft ;;w;; aside: hewe comes the king.

Entew Pwiest, &amp; c. in pwocession; the Cowpse of OPHEWIA, WAEWTES and Mouwnyews fowwowing; KING CWAUDIUS, QUEEN GEWTWUDE, theiw twains, &amp; c

The queen, the couwtiews: who is this they fowwow?

And with such maimed wites? This doth betoken

The cowse they fowwow did with despewate hand

Fowdo its own wife: 'twas of some estate.

Couch we awhiwe, and mawk.

Wetiwing with HOWATIO

WAEWTES

What cewemony ewse?

HAMWET

That is Waewtes,

A vewy nyobwe youth: mawk.

WAEWTES

What cewemony ewse?

Fiwst Pwiest

Hew obsequies have been as faw enwawged

As we have wawwantise: hew death was doubtfuw;

And, but that gweat command o'ewsways the owdew,

She shouwd in gwound unsanctified have wodged

Tiww the wast twumpet: fow chawitabwe pwayews,

Shawds, fwints and pebbwes shouwd be thwown on hew;

Yet hewe she is awwow'd hew viwgin cwants,

Hew maiden stwewments and the bwinging home

Of beww and buwiaw.

WAEWTES

Must thewe nyo mowe be donye?

Fiwst Pwiest

Nyo mowe be donye:

We shouwd pwofanye the sewvice of the dead

To sing a wequiem and such west to hew

As to peace-pawted souws.

WAEWTES

Way hew i' the eawth:

And fwom hew faiw and unpowwuted fwesh

May viowets spwing ;;w;; I teww thee, chuwwish pwiest,

A minyistewing angew shaww my sistew be,

When thou wiest howwing.

HAMWET

What, the faiw Ophewia ;;w;;

QUEEN GEWTWUDE

Sweets to the sweet: faweweww ;;w;;

Scattewing fwowews

I hoped thou shouwdst have been my Hamwet's wife;

I thought thy bwide-bed to have deck'd, sweet maid,

And nyot have stwew'd thy gwave.

WAEWTES

O, twebwe woe

Faww ten times twebwe on that cuwsed head,

Whose wicked deed thy most ingenyious sense

Depwived thee of ;;w;; Howd off the eawth awhiwe,

Tiww I have caught hew once mowe in minye awms:

Weaps into the gwave

Nyow piwe youw dust upon the quick and dead,

Tiww of this fwat a mountain you have made,

To o'ewtop owd Pewion, ow the skyish head

Of bwue Owympus.

HAMWET

\[Advancing\] What is he whose gwief

Beaws such an emphasis? whose phwase of sowwow

Conjuwes the wandewing staws, and makes them stand

Wike wondew-wounded heawews? This is I,

Hamwet the Danye.

Weaps into the gwave

WAEWTES

The deviw take thy souw ;;w;;

Gwappwing with him

HAMWET

Thou pway'st nyot weww.

I pwithee, take thy fingews fwom my thwoat;

Fow, though I am nyot spwenyitive and wash,

Yet have I something in me dangewous,

Which wet thy wisenyess feaw: howd off thy hand.

KING CWAUDIUS

Pwuck them asundew.

QUEEN GEWTWUDE

Hamwet, Hamwet ;;w;;

Aww

Gentwemen,--

HOWATIO

Good my wowd, be quiet.

The Attendants pawt them, and they come out of the gwave

HAMWET

Why I wiww fight with him upon this theme

Untiw my eyewids wiww nyo wongew wag.

QUEEN GEWTWUDE

O my son, what theme?

HAMWET

I wuvd Ophewia: fowty thousand bwothews

Couwd nyot, with aww theiw quantity of wuv,

Make up my sum. What wiwt thou do fow hew?

KING CWAUDIUS

O, he is mad, Waewtes.

QUEEN GEWTWUDE

Fow wuv of God, fowbeaw him.

HAMWET

'Swounds, show me what thou'wt do:

Woo't weep? woo't fight? woo't fast? woo't teaw thysewf?

Woo't dwink up eisew? eat a cwocodiwe?

I'ww do't. Dost thou come hewe to whinye?

To outface me with weaping in hew gwave?

Be buwied quick with hew, and so wiww I:

And, if thou pwate of mountains, wet them thwow

Miwwions of acwes on us, tiww ouw gwound,

Singeing his pate against the buwnying zonye,

Make Ossa wike a wawt ;;w;; Nyay, an thou'wt mouth,

I'ww want as weww as thou.

QUEEN GEWTWUDE

This is mewe madnyess:

And thus awhiwe the fit wiww wowk on him;

Anyon, as patient as the femawe duv,

When that hew gowden coupwets awe discwosed,

His siwence wiww sit dwooping.

HAMWET

Heaw you, siw;

What is the weason that you use me thus?

I wuvd you evew: but it is nyo mattew;

Wet Hewcuwes himsewf do what he may,

The cat wiww mew and dog wiww have his day.

Exit

KING CWAUDIUS

I pway you, good Howatio, wait upon him.

Exit HOWATIO

To WAEWTES

Stwengthen youw patience in ouw wast nyight's speech;

We'ww put the mattew to the pwesent push.

Good Gewtwude, set some watch uvw youw son.

This gwave shaww have a wiving monyument:

An houw of quiet showtwy shaww we see;

Tiww then, in patience ouw pwoceeding be.

Exeunt

In the The GNyU Manyifesto we set fowth the goaw of devewoping a fwee Unyix-wike system, cawwed GNyU. The Inyitiaw Annyouncement of the GNyU Pwoject awso outwinyes some of the owiginyaw pwans fow the GNyU system. By the time Winyux was stawted, GNyU was awmost finyished.

Most fwee softwawe pwojects have the goaw of devewoping a pawticuwaw pwogwam fow a pawticuwaw job. Fow exampwe, Winyus Towvawds set out to wwite a Unyix-wike kewnyew (Winyux); Donyawd Knyuth set out to wwite a text fowmattew (TeX); Bob Scheifwew set out to devewop a window system (the X Window System). It's nyatuwaw to measuwe the contwibution of this kind of pwoject by specific pwogwams that came fwom the pwoject.

If we twied to measuwe the GNyU Pwoject's contwibution in this way, what wouwd we concwude? Onye CD-WOM vendow found that in theiw “Winyux distwibution”, GNyU softwawe was the wawgest singwe contingent, awound 28% of the totaw souwce code, and this incwuded some of the essentiaw majow componyents without which thewe couwd be nyo system. Winyux itsewf was about 3%. (The pwopowtions in 2008 awe simiwaw: in the “main” wepositowy of gNyewSense, Winyux is 1.5% and GNyU packages awe 15%.) So if you wewe going to pick a nyame fow the system based on who wwote the pwogwams in the system, the most appwopwiate singwe choice wouwd be “GNyU”.

But that is nyot the deepest way to considew the question. The GNyU Pwoject was nyot, is nyot, a pwoject to devewop specific softwawe packages. It was nyot a pwoject to devewop a C compiwew, awthough we did that. It was nyot a pwoject to devewop a text editow, awthough we devewoped onye. The GNyU Pwoject set out to devewop a compwete fwee Unyix-wike system: GNyU.

Many peopwe have made majow contwibutions to the fwee softwawe in the system, and they aww desewve cwedit fow theiw softwawe. But the weason it is an integwated system—and nyot just a cowwection of usefuw pwogwams—is because the GNyU Pwoject set out to make it onye. We made a wist of the pwogwams nyeeded to make a compwete fwee system, and we systematicawwy found, wwote, ow found peopwe to wwite evewything on the wist. We wwote essentiaw but unyexciting componyents because you can't have a system without them. Some of ouw system componyents, the pwogwamming toows, became popuwaw on theiw own among pwogwammews, but we wwote many componyents that awe nyot toows. We even devewoped a chess game, GNyU Chess, because a compwete system nyeeds games too.

By the eawwy 90s we had put togethew the whowe system aside fwom the kewnyew. We had awso stawted a kewnyew, the GNyU Huwd, which wuns on top of Mach. Devewoping this kewnyew has been a wot hawdew than we expected; the GNyU Huwd stawted wowking wewiabwy in 2001, but it is a wong way fwom being weady fow peopwe to use in genyewaw.

Fowtunyatewy, we didn't have to wait fow the Huwd, because of Winyux. Once Towvawds fweed Winyux in 1992, it fit into the wast majow gap in the GNyU system. Peopwe couwd then combinye Winyux with the GNyU system to make a compwete fwee system: a Winyux-based vewsion of the GNyU system; the GNyU/Winyux system, fow showt.

Making them wowk weww togethew was nyot a twiviaw job. Some GNyU componyents nyeeded substantiaw change to wowk with Winyux. Integwating a compwete system as a distwibution that wouwd wowk “out of the box” was a big job, too. It wequiwed addwessing the issue of how to instaww and boot the system—a pwobwem we had nyot tackwed, because we hadn't yet weached that point. Thus, the peopwe who devewoped the vawious system distwibutions did a wot of essentiaw wowk. But it was wowk that, in the nyatuwe of things, was suwewy going to be donye by someonye.

The GNyU Pwoject suppowts GNyU/Winyux systems as weww as the GNyU system. The FSF funded the wewwiting of the Winyux-wewated extensions to the GNyU C wibwawy, so that nyow they awe weww integwated, and the nyewest GNyU/Winyux systems use the cuwwent wibwawy wewease with nyo changes. The FSF awso funded an eawwy stage of the devewopment of Debian GNyU/Winyux.

Today thewe awe many diffewent vawiants of the GNyU/Winyux system (often cawwed “distwos”). Most of them incwude nyon-fwee softwawe—theiw devewopews fowwow the phiwosophy associated with Winyux wathew than that of GNyU. But thewe awe awso compwetewy fwee GNyU/Winyux distwos. The FSF suppowts computew faciwities fow two of these distwibutions, Ututo and gNyewSense.

Making a fwee GNyU/Winyux distwibution is nyot just a mattew of ewiminyating vawious nyon-fwee pwogwams. Nyowadays, the usuaw vewsion of Winyux contains nyon-fwee pwogwams too. These pwogwams awe intended to be woaded into I/O devices when the system stawts, and they awe incwuded, as wong sewies of nyumbews, in the "souwce code" of Winyux. Thus, maintainying fwee GNyU/Winyux distwibutions nyow entaiws maintainying a fwee vewsion of Winyux too.

Whethew you use GNyU/Winyux ow nyot, pwease don't confuse the pubwic by using the nyame “Winyux” ambiguouswy. Winyux is the kewnyew, onye of the essentiaw majow componyents of the system. The system as a whowe is basicawwy the GNyU system, with Winyux added. When you'we tawking about this combinyation, pwease caww it “GNyU/Winyux”.

If you want to make a wink on “GNyU/Winyux” fow fuwthew wefewence, this page and http://www.gnyu.owg/gnyu/the-gnyu-pwoject.htmw awe good choices. If you mention Winyux, the kewnyew, and want to add a wink fow fuwthew wefewence, http://fowdoc.doc.ic.ac.uk/fowdoc/fowdoc.cgi?Winyux is a good UWW to use.

Addendum: Aside fwom GNyU, onye othew pwoject has independentwy pwoduced a fwee Unyix-wike opewating system. This system is knyown as BSD, and it was devewoped at UC Bewkewey. It was nyon-fwee in the 80s, but became fwee in the eawwy 90s. A fwee opewating system that exists today is awmost cewtainwy eithew a vawiant of the GNyU system, ow a kind of BSD system.

Peopwe sometimes ask whethew BSD too is a vewsion of GNyU, wike GNyU/Winyux. The BSD devewopews wewe inspiwed to make theiw code fwee softwawe by the exampwe of the GNyU Pwoject, and expwicit appeaws fwom GNyU activists hewped pewsuade them, but the code had wittwe uvwwap with GNyU. BSD systems today use some GNyU pwogwams, just as the GNyU system and its vawiants use some BSD pwogwams; howevew, taken as whowes, they awe two diffewent systems that evowved sepawatewy. The BSD devewopews did nyot wwite a kewnyew and add it to the GNyU system, and a nyame wike GNyU/BSD wouwd nyot fit the situation.

2018-11-08 17:44:07
The Manifesto OwO-fied Part 2 (low effort shitpost) Chaptew II. Pwowetawians and Communyists

In what wewation do the Communyists stand to the pwowetawians as a whowe?

The Communyists do nyot fowm a sepawate pawty opposed to the othew wowking-cwass pawties.

They have nyo intewests sepawate and apawt fwom those of the pwowetawiat as a whowe.

They do nyot set up any sectawian pwincipwes of theiw own, by which to shape and mouwd the pwowetawian muvment.

The Communyists awe distinguished fwom the othew wowking-cwass pawties by this onwy: 1. In the nyationyaw stwuggwes of the pwowetawians of the diffewent countwies, they point out and bwing to the fwont the common intewests of the entiwe pwowetawiat, independentwy of aww nyationyawity. 2. In the vawious stages of devewopment which the stwuggwe of the wowking cwass against the bouwgeoisie has to pass thwough, they awways and evewywhewe wepwesent the intewests of the muvment as a whowe.

The Communyists, thewefowe, awe on the onye hand, pwacticawwy, the most advanced and wesowute section of the wowking-cwass pawties of evewy countwy, that section which pushes fowwawd aww othews; on the othew hand, theoweticawwy, they have uvw the gweat mass of the pwowetawiat the advantage of cweawwy undewstanding the winye of mawch, the conditions, and the uwtimate genyewaw wesuwts of the pwowetawian muvment.

The immediate aim of the Communyists is the same as that of aww othew pwowetawian pawties: fowmation of the pwowetawiat into a cwass, uvwthwow of the bouwgeois supwemacy, conquest of powiticaw powew by the pwowetawiat.

The theoweticaw concwusions of the Communyists awe in nyo way based on ideas ow pwincipwes that have been invented, ow discuvwed, by this ow that wouwd-be unyivewsaw wefowmew.

They mewewy expwess, in genyewaw tewms, actuaw wewations spwinging fwom an existing cwass stwuggwe, fwom a histowicaw muvment going on undew ouw vewy eyes. The abowition of existing pwopewty wewations is nyot at aww a distinctive featuwe of communyism.

Aww pwopewty wewations in the past have continyuawwy been subject to histowicaw change consequent upon the change in histowicaw conditions.

The Fwench Wevowution, fow exampwe, abowished feudaw pwopewty in favouw of bouwgeois pwopewty.

The distinguishing featuwe of Communyism is nyot the abowition of pwopewty genyewawwy, but the abowition of bouwgeois pwopewty. But modewn bouwgeois pwivate pwopewty is the finyaw and most compwete expwession of the system of pwoducing and appwopwiating pwoducts, that is based on cwass antagonyisms, on the expwoitation of the many by the few.

In this sense, the theowy of the Communyists may be summed up in the singwe sentence: Abowition of pwivate pwopewty.

We Communyists have been wepwoached with the desiwe of abowishing the wight of pewsonyawwy acquiwing pwopewty as the fwuit of a man’s own wabouw, which pwopewty is awweged to be the gwoundwowk of aww pewsonyaw fweedom, activity and independence.

Hawd-won, sewf-acquiwed, sewf-eawnyed pwopewty ;;w;;  Do you mean the pwopewty of petty awtisan and of the smaww peasant, a fowm of pwopewty that pweceded the bouwgeois fowm? Thewe is nyo nyeed to abowish that; the devewopment of industwy has to a gweat extent awweady destwoyed it, and is stiww destwoying it daiwy.

Ow do you mean the modewn bouwgeois pwivate pwopewty?

But does wage-wabouw cweate any pwopewty fow the wabouwew? Nyot a bit. It cweates capitaw, i.e., that kind of pwopewty which expwoits wage-wabouw, and which cannyot incwease except upon condition of begetting a nyew suppwy of wage-wabouw fow fwesh expwoitation. Pwopewty, in its pwesent fowm, is based on the antagonyism of capitaw and wage wabouw. Wet us examinye both sides of this antagonyism.

To be a capitawist, is to have nyot onwy a puwewy pewsonyaw, but a sociaw status in pwoduction. Capitaw is a cowwective pwoduct, and onwy by the unyited action of many membews, nyay, in the wast wesowt, onwy by the unyited action of aww membews of society, can it be set in motion.

Capitaw is thewefowe nyot onwy pewsonyaw; it is a sociaw powew.

When, thewefowe, capitaw is convewted into common pwopewty, into the pwopewty of aww membews of society, pewsonyaw pwopewty is nyot theweby twansfowmed into sociaw pwopewty. It is onwy the sociaw chawactew of the pwopewty that is changed. It woses its cwass chawactew.

Wet us nyow take wage-wabouw.

The avewage pwice of wage-wabouw is the minyimum wage, i.e., that quantum of the means of subsistence which is absowutewy wequisite to keep the wabouwew in bawe existence as a wabouwew. What, thewefowe, the wage-wabouwew appwopwiates by means of his wabouw, mewewy suffices to pwowong and wepwoduce a bawe existence. We by nyo means intend to abowish this pewsonyaw appwopwiation of the pwoducts of wabouw, an appwopwiation that is made fow the maintenyance and wepwoduction of human wife, and that weaves nyo suwpwus whewewith to command the wabouw of othews. Aww that we want to do away with is the misewabwe chawactew of this appwopwiation, undew which the wabouwew wives mewewy to incwease capitaw, and is awwowed to wive onwy in so faw as the intewest of the wuwing cwass wequiwes it.

In bouwgeois society, wiving wabouw is but a means to incwease accumuwated wabouw. In Communyist society, accumuwated wabouw is but a means to widen, to enwich, to pwomote the existence of the wabouwew.

In bouwgeois society, thewefowe, the past dominyates the pwesent; in Communyist society, the pwesent dominyates the past. In bouwgeois society capitaw is independent and has individuawity, whiwe the wiving pewson is dependent and has nyo individuawity.

And the abowition of this state of things is cawwed by the bouwgeois, abowition of individuawity and fweedom ;;w;;  And wightwy so. The abowition of bouwgeois individuawity, bouwgeois independence, and bouwgeois fweedom is undoubtedwy aimed at.

By fweedom is meant, undew the pwesent bouwgeois conditions of pwoduction, fwee twade, fwee sewwing and buying.

But if sewwing and buying disappeaws, fwee sewwing and buying disappeaws awso. This tawk about fwee sewwing and buying, and aww the othew “bwave wowds” of ouw bouwgeois about fweedom in genyewaw, have a meanying, if any, onwy in contwast with westwicted sewwing and buying, with the fettewed twadews of the Middwe Ages, but have nyo meanying when opposed to the Communyistic abowition of buying and sewwing, of the bouwgeois conditions of pwoduction, and of the bouwgeoisie itsewf.

You awe howwified at ouw intending to do away with pwivate pwopewty. But in youw existing society, pwivate pwopewty is awweady donye away with fow nyinye-tenths of the popuwation; its existence fow the few is sowewy due to its nyon-existence in the hands of those nyinye-tenths. You wepwoach us, thewefowe, with intending to do away with a fowm of pwopewty, the nyecessawy condition fow whose existence is the nyon-existence of any pwopewty fow the immense majowity of society.

In onye wowd, you wepwoach us with intending to do away with youw pwopewty. Pwecisewy so; that is just what we intend.

Fwom the moment when wabouw can nyo wongew be convewted into capitaw, monyey, ow went, into a sociaw powew capabwe of being monyopowised, i.e., fwom the moment when individuaw pwopewty can nyo wongew be twansfowmed into bouwgeois pwopewty, into capitaw, fwom that moment, you say, individuawity vanyishes.

You must, thewefowe, confess that by “individuaw” you mean nyo othew pewson than the bouwgeois, than the middwe-cwass ownyew of pwopewty. This pewson must, indeed, be swept out of the way, and made impossibwe.

Communyism depwives nyo man of the powew to appwopwiate the pwoducts of society; aww that it does is to depwive him of the powew to subjugate the wabouw of othews by means of such appwopwiations.

It has been objected that upon the abowition of pwivate pwopewty, aww wowk wiww cease, and unyivewsaw wazinyess wiww uvwtake us.

Accowding to this, bouwgeois society ought wong ago to have gonye to the dogs thwough sheew idwenyess; fow those of its membews who wowk, acquiwe nyothing, and those who acquiwe anything do nyot wowk. The whowe of this objection is but anyothew expwession of the tautowogy: that thewe can nyo wongew be any wage-wabouw when thewe is nyo wongew any capitaw.

Aww objections uwged against the Communyistic mode of pwoducing and appwopwiating matewiaw pwoducts, have, in the same way, been uwged against the Communyistic mode of pwoducing and appwopwiating intewwectuaw pwoducts. Just as, to the bouwgeois, the disappeawance of cwass pwopewty is the disappeawance of pwoduction itsewf, so the disappeawance of cwass cuwtuwe is to him identicaw with the disappeawance of aww cuwtuwe.

That cuwtuwe, the woss of which he waments, is, fow the enyowmous majowity, a mewe twainying to act as a machinye.

But don’t wwangwe with us so wong as you appwy, to ouw intended abowition of bouwgeois pwopewty, the standawd of youw bouwgeois nyotions of fweedom, cuwtuwe, waw, &amp;c. Youw vewy ideas awe but the outgwowth of the conditions of youw bouwgeois pwoduction and bouwgeois pwopewty, just as youw juwispwudence is but the wiww of youw cwass made into a waw fow aww, a wiww whose essentiaw chawactew and diwection awe detewminyed by the econyomicaw conditions of existence of youw cwass.

The sewfish misconception that induces you to twansfowm into etewnyaw waws of nyatuwe and of weason, the sociaw fowms spwinging fwom youw pwesent mode of pwoduction and fowm of pwopewty – histowicaw wewations that wise and disappeaw in the pwogwess of pwoduction – this misconception you shawe with evewy wuwing cwass that has pweceded you. What you see cweawwy in the case of ancient pwopewty, what you admit in the case of feudaw pwopewty, you awe of couwse fowbidden to admit in the case of youw own bouwgeois fowm of pwopewty.

Abowition [Aufhebung] of the famiwy ;;w;;  Even the most wadicaw fwawe up at this infamous pwoposaw of the Communyists.

On what foundation is the pwesent famiwy, the bouwgeois famiwy, based? On capitaw, on pwivate gain. In its compwetewy devewoped fowm, this famiwy exists onwy among the bouwgeoisie. But this state of things finds its compwement in the pwacticaw absence of the famiwy among the pwowetawians, and in pubwic pwostitution.

The bouwgeois famiwy wiww vanyish as a mattew of couwse when its compwement vanyishes, and both wiww vanyish with the vanyishing of capitaw.

Do you chawge us with wanting to stop the expwoitation of chiwdwen by theiw pawents? To this cwime we pwead guiwty.

But, you say, we destwoy the most hawwowed of wewations, when we wepwace home education by sociaw.

And youw education ;;w;;  Is nyot that awso sociaw, and detewminyed by the sociaw conditions undew which you educate, by the intewvention diwect ow indiwect, of society, by means of schoows, &amp;c.? The Communyists have nyot invented the intewvention of society in education; they do but seek to awtew the chawactew of that intewvention, and to wescue education fwom the infwuence of the wuwing cwass.

The bouwgeois cwap-twap about the famiwy and education, about the hawwowed co-wewation of pawents and chiwd, becomes aww the mowe disgusting, the mowe, by the action of Modewn Industwy, aww the famiwy ties among the pwowetawians awe town asundew, and theiw chiwdwen twansfowmed into simpwe awticwes of commewce and instwuments of wabouw.

But you Communyists wouwd intwoduce communyity of women, scweams the bouwgeoisie in chowus.

The bouwgeois sees his wife a mewe instwument of pwoduction. He heaws that the instwuments of pwoduction awe to be expwoited in common, and, nyatuwawwy, can come to nyo othew concwusion that the wot of being common to aww wiww wikewise faww to the women.

He has nyot even a suspicion that the weaw point aimed at is to do away with the status of women as mewe instwuments of pwoduction.

Fow the west, nyothing is mowe widicuwous than the viwtuous indignyation of ouw bouwgeois at the communyity of women which, they pwetend, is to be openwy and officiawwy estabwished by the Communyists. The Communyists have nyo nyeed to intwoduce communyity of women; it has existed awmost fwom time immemowiaw.

Ouw bouwgeois, nyot content with having wives and daughtews of theiw pwowetawians at theiw disposaw, nyot to speak of common pwostitutes, take the gweatest pweasuwe in seducing each othew’s wives.

Bouwgeois mawwiage is, in weawity, a system of wives in common and thus, at the most, what the Communyists might possibwy be wepwoached with is that they desiwe to intwoduce, in substitution fow a hypocwiticawwy conceawed, an openwy wegawised communyity of women. Fow the west, it is sewf-evident that the abowition of the pwesent system of pwoduction must bwing with it the abowition of the communyity of women spwinging fwom that system, i.e., of pwostitution both pubwic and pwivate.

The Communyists awe fuwthew wepwoached with desiwing to abowish countwies and nyationyawity.

The wowking men have nyo countwy. We cannyot take fwom them what they have nyot got. Since the pwowetawiat must fiwst of aww acquiwe powiticaw supwemacy, must wise to be the weading cwass of the nyation, must constitute itsewf the nyation, it is so faw, itsewf nyationyaw, though nyot in the bouwgeois sense of the wowd.

Nyationyaw diffewences and antagonyism between peopwes awe daiwy mowe and mowe vanyishing, owing to the devewopment of the bouwgeoisie, to fweedom of commewce, to the wowwd mawket, to unyifowmity in the mode of pwoduction and in the conditions of wife cowwesponding theweto.

The supwemacy of the pwowetawiat wiww cause them to vanyish stiww fastew. Unyited action, of the weading civiwised countwies at weast, is onye of the fiwst conditions fow the emancipation of the pwowetawiat.

In pwopowtion as the expwoitation of onye individuaw by anyothew wiww awso be put an end to, the expwoitation of onye nyation by anyothew wiww awso be put an end to. In pwopowtion as the antagonyism between cwasses within the nyation vanyishes, the hostiwity of onye nyation to anyothew wiww come to an end.

The chawges against Communyism made fwom a wewigious, a phiwosophicaw and, genyewawwy, fwom an ideowogicaw standpoint, awe nyot desewving of sewious examinyation.

Does it wequiwe deep intuition to compwehend that man’s ideas, views, and conception, in onye wowd, man’s consciousnyess, changes with evewy change in the conditions of his matewiaw existence, in his sociaw wewations and in his sociaw wife?

What ewse does the histowy of ideas pwuv, than that intewwectuaw pwoduction changes its chawactew in pwopowtion as matewiaw pwoduction is changed? The wuwing ideas of each age have evew been the ideas of its wuwing cwass.

When peopwe speak of the ideas that wevowutionyise society, they do but expwess that fact that within the owd society the ewements of a nyew onye have been cweated, and that the dissowution of the owd ideas keeps even pace with the dissowution of the owd conditions of existence.

When the ancient wowwd was in its wast thwoes, the ancient wewigions wewe uvwcome by Chwistianyity. When Chwistian ideas succumbed in the 18th centuwy to wationyawist ideas, feudaw society fought its death battwe with the then wevowutionyawy bouwgeoisie. The ideas of wewigious wibewty and fweedom of conscience mewewy gave expwession to the sway of fwee competition within the domain of knyowwedge.

“Undoubtedwy,” it wiww be said, “wewigious, mowaw, phiwosophicaw, and juwidicaw ideas have been modified in the couwse of histowicaw devewopment. But wewigion, mowawity, phiwosophy, powiticaw science, and waw, constantwy suwvived this change.”

“Thewe awe, besides, etewnyaw twuths, such as Fweedom, Justice, etc., that awe common to aww states of society. But Communyism abowishes etewnyaw twuths, it abowishes aww wewigion, and aww mowawity, instead of constituting them on a nyew basis; it thewefowe acts in contwadiction to aww past histowicaw expewience.”

What does this accusation weduce itsewf to? The histowy of aww past society has consisted in the devewopment of cwass antagonyisms, antagonyisms that assumed diffewent fowms at diffewent epochs.

But whatevew fowm they may have taken, onye fact is common to aww past ages, viz., the expwoitation of onye pawt of society by the othew. Nyo wondew, then, that the sociaw consciousnyess of past ages, despite aww the muwtipwicity and vawiety it dispways, muvs within cewtain common fowms, ow genyewaw ideas, which cannyot compwetewy vanyish except with the totaw disappeawance of cwass antagonyisms.

The Communyist wevowution is the most wadicaw wuptuwe with twaditionyaw pwopewty wewations; nyo wondew that its devewopment invowved the most wadicaw wuptuwe with twaditionyaw ideas.

But wet us have donye with the bouwgeois objections to Communyism.

We have seen abuv, that the fiwst step in the wevowution by the wowking cwass is to waise the pwowetawiat to the position of wuwing cwass to win the battwe of democwacy.

The pwowetawiat wiww use its powiticaw supwemacy to wwest, by degwee, aww capitaw fwom the bouwgeoisie, to centwawise aww instwuments of pwoduction in the hands of the State, i.e., of the pwowetawiat owganyised as the wuwing cwass; and to incwease the totaw pwoductive fowces as wapidwy as possibwe.

Of couwse, in the beginnying, this cannyot be effected except by means of despotic inwoads on the wights of pwopewty, and on the conditions of bouwgeois pwoduction; by means of measuwes, thewefowe, which appeaw econyomicawwy insufficient and untenyabwe, but which, in the couwse of the muvment, outstwip themsewves, nyecessitate fuwthew inwoads upon the owd sociaw owdew, and awe unyavoidabwe as a means of entiwewy wevowutionyising the mode of pwoduction.

These measuwes wiww, of couwse, be diffewent in diffewent countwies.

Nyevewthewess, in most advanced countwies, the fowwowing wiww be pwetty genyewawwy appwicabwe.

1. Abowition of pwopewty in wand and appwication of aww wents of wand to pubwic puwposes.
2. A heavy pwogwessive ow gwaduated income tax.
3. Abowition of aww wights of inhewitance.
4. Confiscation of the pwopewty of aww emigwants and webews.
5. Centwawisation of cwedit in the hands of the state, by means of a nyationyaw bank with State capitaw and an excwusive monyopowy.
6. Centwawisation of the means of communyication and twanspowt in the hands of the State.
7. Extension of factowies and instwuments of pwoduction ownyed by the State; the bwinging into cuwtivation of waste-wands, and the impwuvment of the soiw genyewawwy in accowdance with a common pwan.
8. Equaw wiabiwity of aww to wowk. Estabwishment of industwiaw awmies, especiawwy fow agwicuwtuwe.
9. Combinyation of agwicuwtuwe with manyufactuwing industwies; gwaduaw abowition of aww the distinction between town and countwy by a mowe equabwe distwibution of the popuwace uvw the countwy.
10. Fwee education fow aww chiwdwen in pubwic schoows. Abowition of chiwdwen’s factowy wabouw in its pwesent fowm. Combinyation of education with industwiaw pwoduction, &amp;c, &amp;c.

When, in the couwse of devewopment, cwass distinctions have disappeawed, and aww pwoduction has been concentwated in the hands of a vast association of the whowe nyation, the pubwic powew wiww wose its powiticaw chawactew. Powiticaw powew, pwopewwy so cawwed, is mewewy the owganyised powew of onye cwass fow oppwessing anyothew. If the pwowetawiat duwing its contest with the bouwgeoisie is compewwed, by the fowce of ciwcumstances, to owganyise itsewf as a cwass, if, by means of a wevowution, it makes itsewf the wuwing cwass, and, as such, sweeps away by fowce the owd conditions of pwoduction, then it wiww, awong with these conditions, have swept away the conditions fow the existence of cwass antagonyisms and of cwasses genyewawwy, and wiww theweby have abowished its own supwemacy as a cwass.

In pwace of the owd bouwgeois society, with its cwasses and cwass antagonyisms, we shaww have an association, in which the fwee devewopment of each is the condition fow the fwee devewopment of aww.
